---
import MainLayout from '../../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import MotuSidebar from '../../../components/MotuSidebar.astro';
const title = "MIDI";
---
<MainLayout title={title}>
  <div class="flex gap-8 items-start">
    <div class="w-[250px] flex-shrink-0">
      <MotuSidebar />
    </div>
    <article class="prose max-w-none">
      <h1>{title}</h1>
      <p>Source: <a href="https://motu.com/products/motuaudio/ultralite-mk3/midi.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MOTU product page</a></p>

      <p>The UltraLite-mk3 includes one 5-pin MIDI DIN In port and one 5-pin MIDI DIN Out port on the rear panel. These appear in Ableton as separate MIDI input and output devices, enabling hardware MIDI routing alongside USB MIDI controllers.</p>

      <h2>Routing Scenarios</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Hydrasynth MIDI DIN → MOTU MIDI In → Ableton:</strong> use when the Hydrasynth's USB connection is occupied for audio, or to separate MIDI from audio on different physical connections. The Hydrasynth routes through the MOTU MIDI In and appears in Ableton as a standard MIDI input device.</li>
        <li><strong>Yamaha P-225 MIDI Out → MOTU MIDI In → Ableton:</strong> the P-225's 5-pin MIDI output provides an alternative to USB when USB is used for another purpose. Route the P-225's DIN output into the MOTU MIDI In for a hardware MIDI path to Ableton.</li>
        <li><strong>Launchkey 37 MIDI Out → Hydrasynth MIDI In (direct):</strong> for standalone jams without a computer. Connect a 5-pin DIN cable directly from the Launchkey 37's MIDI Out to the Hydrasynth's MIDI In. The MOTU is not in this chain — it's a pure hardware-to-hardware connection. Use the Launchkey's Scale Mode to perform in-key on the Hydrasynth with no computer involved.</li>
        <li><strong>Ableton MIDI Out → MOTU MIDI Out → Hydrasynth MIDI In:</strong> send MIDI sequences, automation CC messages, or patch changes from Ableton directly to the Hydrasynth through the MOTU's DIN Out. Useful when MIDI routing complex sequences to the Hydrasynth while keeping USB free for audio.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>MIDI Thru in CueMix FX</h2>
      <p>In CueMix FX settings, MIDI Thru can be enabled to simultaneously forward incoming MIDI DIN data to both the software (Ableton) and the MIDI DIN Out port. This creates a daisy-chain: a controller can drive Ableton via MOTU MIDI In while simultaneously controlling a hardware synth connected to MOTU MIDI Out.</p>

      <figure>
        <img src="https://cdn-data.motu.com/site/images/ultralite-mk3/midi-connections_01.gif" alt="UltraLite-mk3 MIDI connections" />
        <figcaption>Official MOTU-hosted MIDI connections diagram.</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </article>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
